If measure= ¡°P¡±, \(M_{P} = \\frac{m-\sum_{i=1}^m P_{ii}}{m-1}\) ;
if measure = ¡°D¡±, \(M_{D} = 1 - |\det(P)|\) ,
where \(\det(P)\) is the determinant of \(P\) ;
if measure = ¡°L2¡±, \(M_{L2} = 1  - |\lambda_2|\) ,
where \(\lambda_2\) is the second largest eigenvalue of \(P\) ;
if measure = ¡°B1¡±, \(M_{B1} = \\frac{m-m \sum_{i=1}^m \pi_i P_{ii}}{m-1}\) ,
where \(\pi\) is the initial income distribution;
if measure == ¡°B2¡±, \(M_{B2} = \\frac{1}{m-1} \sum_{i=1}^m \sum_{
j=1}^m \pi_i P_{ij} |i-j|\) ,
where \(\pi\) is the initial income distribution.

